This paper proposes a neural network architecture for response selection in conversational dialogue, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and specifically, dialogue systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses a bi-directional GRU for encoding context and responses, which is a common technique in deep learning and falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also incorporates attention mechanisms, which is a popular technique in machine learning and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also uses external knowledge in the form of domain-specific keywords, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper uses a GRU for encoding the domain keyword descriptions, which is a technique in neural networks and falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
